This package implements the LJ 12-6-4 potential as a LAMMPS pair style.

=========================================================================

Use "make yes-user-lj1264" to enable this package when building LAMMPS.

The package implements two pair styles: lj/1264/cut and lj/1264/cut/coul/cut

pair_style lj1264/cut <cutoff>
pair_coeff <itype> <jtype> <sigma> <epsilon> <c> <cutoff>

or

pair_style lj1264/cut/coul/cut <lj cutoff> <coul cutoff>
pair_coeff <itype> <jtype> <sigma> <epsilon> <c4> <lj cutoff>  <coul cutoff>


Example of usage

```
pair_style lj1264/cut 3.0
pair_coeff 1 1 1.0 1.0 1.0 3.0
```


References:
 - Pengfei, Li; Son, Lin Frank; Merz Jr., Kenneth M. (2015), "Parameterization of Highly Charged Metal Ions Using the 12-6‑4 LJ-Type Nonbonded Model in Explicit Water", Journal of Physical Chemistry B, 119: 883–895, doi:10.1021/jp505875v
 - Pengfei, Li; Merz Jr., Kenneth M. (2014), "Taking into Account the Ion-induced Dipole Interaction in the Nonbonded Model of Ions", Journal of Chemical Theory and Computation, 10 (1): 289–297, doi:10.1021/ct400751u, PMC 3960013
